SIMPLE: repent
RECORDS: 3

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Repent
<hw>Re"pent</hw> <pr>(r?"p?nt)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>repens</ets>, <ets>-entis</ets>, creeping, p. pr. of
<ets>repere</ets> to creep.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Bot.)</fld>
<def>Prostrate and rooting; -- said of stems.</def>
<rj><au>Gray.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>Same as
<er>Reptant</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Repent</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Repent
<hw>Re*pent"</hw> <pr>(r?-p?nt")</pr>, <pos>v. i.</pos>
<vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos> <conjf>Repented</conjf>; <pos>p. pr. &
vb. n.</pos> <conjf>Repenting</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[F. <ets>se
repentir</ets>; L. pref. <ets>re-</ets> re- + <ets>poenitere</ets> to
make repent, <ets>poenitet me</ets> it repents me, I repent. See
<er>Penitent</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To feel pain, sorrow, or
regret, for what one has done or omitted to do.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>First she relents⟦br⟧
With pity; of that pity then <qex>repents</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Dryden.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To change the mind, or the course of conduct, on
account of regret or dissatisfaction.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Lest, peradventure, the people <qex>repent</qex> when they see
war, and they return to Egypt.</q> <rj><qau>Ex. xiii. 17.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Theol.)</fld> <def>To be sorry for sin as morally
evil, and to seek forgiveness; to cease to love and practice
sin.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Except ye <qex>repent</qex>, ye shall likewise perish.</q>
<rj><qau>Luke xii. 3.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Repent</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Repent
<hw>Re*pent"</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To feel pain on
account of; to remember with sorrow.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>I do <qex>repent</qex> it from my very soul.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><-- p. 1220 --></p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To feel regret or sorrow; -- used
reflexively.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>My father has <qex>repented</qex> him ere now.</q>
<rj><qau>Dryden.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>To cause to have sorrow or regret; -- used
impersonally.</def> <mark>[Archaic]</mark> ⟦ldquo⟧And it
<xex>repented</xex> the Lord that he had made man on the earth.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Gen. vi. 6.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Repentance</ent>⟦br⟧
